<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00037</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT ESTABLISHING A FREE IRRIGATION PROGRAM, REPEALING SECTION 2, PARAGRAPH (C) OF REPUBLIC ACT NO. 3601 OR "AN ACT CREATING THE NATIONAL IRRIGATION ADMINISTRATION"; SECTION 1, PARAGRAPH (B) OF PRESIDENTIAL DECREE NO. 552; SECTION 1, PARAGRAPH (B) PRESIDENTIAL DECREE NO. 1702; SECTION 35 OF REPUBLIC ACT NO. 8435, OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE "AGRICULTURAL AND FISHERIES MODERNIZATION LAW"; AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : Free Irrigation Law Of 2016</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Creates a Free Irrigation Program (FIP) for the farmers in order to increase their incomes and uplift their living conditions, thereby effectively abolishing the Irrigation Service Fee (ISF) imposed on the farmers.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>YAP, ARTHUR C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-06-30</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>NATURE : Economic</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Roque (H.) (002 2016-07-26)</td><td>2. Fortun (010 2016-08-15)</td><tr><td>3. Abayon (012 2016-08-17)</td><td>4. Antonio (014 2016-08-23)</td><tr><td>5. Espino (023 2016-09-19)</td><td>6. Bravo (M.) (023 2016-09-19)</td><tr><td>7. Sarmiento (C.) (024 2016-09-20)</td><td>8. Villanueva (042 2016-11-09)</td><tr><td>9. Marcoleta (045 2016-11-16)</td><td>10. Lobregat (046 2016-11-21)</td><tr><td>11. Sy-Alvarado (046 2016-11-21)</td><td>12. Lee (046 2016-11-21)</td><tr><td>13. Gonzaga (046 2016-11-21)</td><td>14. Lazatin (048 2016-11-23)</td><tr><td>15. Relampagos (048 2016-11-23)</td><td>16. Kho (048 2016-11-23)</td><tr><td>17. Abu (048 2016-11-23)</td><td>18. Bordado (057 2017-01-16)</td><tr><td>19. Angara-Castillo (062 2017-01-25)</td><td>20. Limkaichong (063 2017-01-30)</td><tr><td>21. Nava (074 2017-